modules.description: Compares and combines bounds for interval management, supporting lower and upper bound comparisons and selection. Operates on a type representing bounded values, such as numeric ranges or symbolic limits. Used to determine overlapping intervals or adjust bound constraints in constraint satisfaction problems.

Creates and compares intervals based on lower and upper bounds, ensuring valid range definitions. Computes overlapping regions between intervals or checks for intersection existence. Operates on interval structures defined by ordered bounds, supporting precise spatial or temporal range analysis.

Generates intervals and associated values, allowing traversal of a sequence of time-based segments with associated data. It processes elements in batches defined by intervals, supporting accumulation over these segments. Used for iterating through time-sliced data structures while maintaining state between steps.

Compares two values of type t using a lexicographical ordering, returning -1, 0, or 1 based on their relationship. It operates on opaque type t, which represents structured data suitable for ordered comparisons. This function is used to sort lists of t values or determine precedence in rule-based systems.

Provides operations to insert, query, and remove intervals with associated values, supporting inclusive, exclusive, and unbounded bounds. Works with interval trees where each node represents a range and stores one or more values. Used to efficiently find all values overlapping a specific time range or numerical span.

Compares interval-based data structures by their order, returning a signed integer based on their relative positions. Operates on a custom type representing intervals, enabling precise ordering and comparison. Used to determine the sequence of non-overlapping intervals in scheduling or range-based computations.
